Alberico da Barbiano (c. 1344 â€“ 1409) was the first of the Italian condottieri. His master in military matters was the English mercenary John Hawkwood, known in Italy as Giovanni Acuto. Alberico's "compagnia" fought under the banner of Saint George, as the "compagnia San Giorgio".
